[SEVERITY: HIGH] System: DarkEpilogueScene \'97 Issue: SMOKE_POOL.length=0 and EX_POOL.length=0 are not called before transitioning back to the WorldMap, leading to potential memory leaks. \'97 Fix: Add SMOKE_POOL.length=0; EX_POOL.length=0; to both the LHCEpilogue exit logic and the DarkEpilogue exit logic.\
[SEVERITY: MED] System: DarkEpilogueScene \'97 Issue: The _mandelaFlash(self) call at t=12000ms can trigger after the scene has been destroyed if the player skips early, causing a crash. \'97 Fix: Wrap the internal flash logic in an if(!self._done) guard.\
[SEVERITY: LOW] System: DarkEpilogueScene \'97 Issue: Tween-animated text objects might not be garbage collected immediately if tweens overlap with scene exits. \'97 Fix: Call .destroy() on text objects in the onComplete handlers of their tweens. Ensure setScrollFactor(0) and setDepth() are explicitly applied.\
[SEVERITY: HIGH] System: DarkEpilogueScene \'97 Issue: this.keys.z is not initialized and the update loop lacks a this._done check, allowing double-triggering or errors on Z press. \'97 Fix: Initialize this.keys = \{z: this.input.keyboard.addKey('Z')\} in create() and check if (!this._done && Phaser.Input.Keyboard.JustDown(this.keys.z)) in update().\
[SEVERITY: MED] System: _drawAnomalyOverlay \'97 Issue: Using scene._anomalyTimer = (scene._anomalyTimer||0) - 16 assumes a fixed 60fps, causing inconsistent timer behavior on varying refresh rates. \'97 Fix: Pass the delta time as a parameter _drawAnomalyOverlay(scene, delta) and subtract delta instead of 16.\
[SEVERITY: MED] System: _drawAnomalyOverlay \'97 Issue: scene.anomalyG.clear() only runs when mandela >= 10, meaning old graphics persist if the condition evaluates to false later. \'97 Fix: Move scene.anomalyG.clear() to the top of the function so it clears every frame unconditionally.\
[SEVERITY: LOW] System: _drawAnomalyOverlay \'97 Issue: text.destroy() in the tween onComplete handler will throw an error if the scene transitions mid-tween. \'97 Fix: Wrap the destroy call in a try/catch block: try \{ txt.destroy(); \} catch(e) \{\}.\
[SEVERITY: HIGH] System: _drawAnomalyOverlay \'97 Issue: Variables scene.mapOffX and scene.tW might not exist on all WorldMap scenes, causing undefined errors. \'97 Fix: Use fallback values like var offX = scene.mapOffX || scene.offX || 0; and var tW = scene.tW || 32;.\
[SEVERITY: HIGH] System: Level63/64 onUpdate hooks \'97 Issue: scene.edPx is referenced, but the factory creates the player physics object as scene.ep, leading to undefined reference errors. \'97 Fix: Change the reference from scene.edPx.x to scene.ep ? scene.ep.x : 0.\
[SEVERITY: LOW] System: Level63/64 onUpdate hooks \'97 Issue: if(!scene._rbFlags)scene._rbFlags=\{\} runs every frame, which is safe but wasteful. \'97 Fix: Move the initialization of scene._rbFlags = \{\} to the onCreate hook instead of onUpdate.\
